Read less
We have added functionality to some of our connected products which allows your Dyson product to interact with certain third party products that you have in your home (such as Amazon Echo, otherwise known as Alexa). This functionality allows you to take full advantage of a “smart home” environment. However, the products will only interact if you want them to, by enabling the relevant functionality.
If you choose to allow your Dyson connected product to interact with a third party product, certain information (including potentially personal data) will need to be shared with the third party product and the relevant third party provider. Generally, we will need to share a unique reference number to connect the two products, and information about your product and how you use it. We only share the minimum amount of personal data that we need, to enable the two products to interact.  Details of how the third party uses your personal data (as well as any personal data which it collects through its own product) are set out in the third party's privacy notice. You should carefully review third parties' privacy notice(s) before using their products, and before connecting them with your Dyson connected product. You can stop your Dyson connected product from sharing information with the third party product at any time by disabling the connection between the two.
See
Dyson smart machines
for further information specific to your product.
